This is a severe bug in ImageRegistry.put(String, Image): the key is not stored
in the table which causes clients to create the image over and over again.

        if (entry == null) {
            entry = new Entry();
        }

should be:

        if (entry == null) {
            entry = new Entry();
            putEntry(key, entry);
        }

Note: There are several open bug reports related to "no more handles" which are
most likely caused by this bug as well.
